		<hr />
		<div class="text-section">
			<span class="section-header">Abilities<br /></span>
			<div class="wiki-info">
				In the beginning of the game the Banshee chooses a player as target.
				Only when the current target dies or leaves the game, a new player is chosen.
				<br />The target is the only player who can die during a hunt. 
				<b>BUT</b> if the target is outside the investigation area, the Banshee can kill anyone.
				<br /><br />
				When performing a roam and the target is inside the investigation area, 
				the Banshee has a 67% chance to long roam to the target. This will not create any EMF reading.
				<br />This ability will fail, if the ghost and target are on different floors except if:
				<ul>
					<li>The map is 'Point Hope'.</li>
					<li>The Banshee is in a single-room basement or attic.</li>
				</ul>
				<br />Banshees prefer singing ghost events. If the hunt-target is also the event-target and ends such an event prematurely, 
				they will lose 15% sanity instead of the normal 10%.
				<br /><br />When in a D.O.T.S. state, the Banshee will try to move towards its target instead of the nearest player.
				<br /><br />There is a 33% chance of getting 1 out of 20 unique screams (= banshee screams) instead of a normal sound
				while using a Parabolic Microphone or Sound Recorder.
			</div>
		</div>
